<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>DutchNews.nl</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/</link><description>DutchNews.nl brings daily news from The Netherlands in English</description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 13:42:59 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Five injured, one hospitalised after gas explosion at school</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/03/five-injured-one-hospitalised-after-gas-explosion-at-school/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-265715 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-accidents category-schools"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Five injured, one hospitalised after gas explosion at school</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-03-27T13:42:30+00:00"> March 27, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-265716" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_265716"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="674" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/ANP-554480296.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/ANP-554480296.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/ANP-554480296-560x377.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/ANP-554480296-768x518.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-265716"> The emergency services outside the school. Photo: Iris van den Broek ANP</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Five people have been injured after a cloud of gas ignited during a pancake event at a secondary school in Oosterhout in Brabant.</p><section class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none [--shadow-height:45px] has-data-writing-block:pointer-events-none has-data-writing-block:-mt-(--shadow-height) has-data-writing-block:pt-(--shadow-height) [&amp;:has([data-writing-block])&gt;*]:pointer-events-auto scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" data-scroll-anchor="true" data-testid="conversation-turn-24" data-turn="assistant" data-turn-id="request-WEB:9b9c1cd4-a883-442d-9cdd-b590add4f8c3-11" dir="auto"><div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto pb-10 [--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-xs,calc(var(--spacing)*4))] @w-sm/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-sm,calc(var(--spacing)*6))] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-margin:var(--thread-content-margin-lg,calc(var(--spacing)*16))] px-(--thread-content-margin)"><div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] @w-lg/main:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn"><div class="flex max-w-full flex-col gap-4 grow"><div class="min-h-8 text-message relative flex w-full flex-col items-end gap-2 text-start break-words whitespace-normal outline-none keyboard-focused:focus-ring [.text-message+&amp;]:mt-1" data-message-author-role="assistant" data-message-id="061e2ff8-2be5-4798-8aae-2de4ebf6d333" data-message-model-slug="gpt-5-3" data-turn-start-message="true" dir="auto" tabindex="0"><div class="flex w-full flex-col gap-1 empty:hidden"><div class="markdown prose dark:prose-invert w-full wrap-break-word light markdown-new-styling"><p data-end="466" data-start="169">The incident took place in a professional kitchen at a practical education school on Nassaustraat. One person was seriously injured and taken to hospital, while four others suffered burns and were treated at the scene.</p><p data-end="574" data-start="468">Both students and adults were among the injured.</p><p data-end="974" data-start="763">Initial reports suggested an explosion involving a gas cylinder and seven casualties, but authorities later said the incident was likely caused by a gas leak that ignited. Police are investigating.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/accidents/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/schools/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=265715</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 13:42:30 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>EU parliament calls for ban on AI nudity-generating apps</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/03/eu-parliament-calls-for-ban-on-ai-nudity-generating-apps/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-265636 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-dutch-european-news category-sexual-abuse category-tech"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> EU parliament calls for ban on AI nudity-generating apps</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-03-27T13:25:34+00:00"> March 27, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-233678" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_233678"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="426" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/P036088000802-592605.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/P036088000802-592605.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/P036088000802-592605-560x373.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/P036088000802-592605-360x240.jpg 360w" width="640"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-233678"> Photo: EU audiovisual service</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The European parliament has called for a ban on AI apps that allow to create nude or sexually explicit audiovisual material based on the photo of a real person, without consent.</p><p>MEPs on Thursday voted in favour of on a <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2025/11/brussels-proposes-relaxing-data-protection-to-support-tech-firms/">Commission proposal</a> to simplify and delay the application of certain artificial intelligence rules.</p><p>The amendment follows controversy around Grok, X’s AI assistant, which at the beginning of the year allowed the mass production and dissemination of fake nude images based on real people’s photos.</p><p>A Dutch court has just ruled that the <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/03/dutch-ban-elon-musks-grok-undressing-app-over-abusive-images/">app must be disabled in the Netherlands</a>. Generating sexual images of minors is covered by Dutch legislation on online sexual abuse.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The Center for Countering Digital Hate, a British-American non-profit, estimates that three million sexualised images, including of minors, were generated in less than two weeks.</p><p>In January the European Commission opened an investigation into the app under the <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2025/12/eu-commission-slaps-fine-on-x-over-deceptive-practices/">Digital Service Act (DSA)</a>.</p><p>“This ban on ‘nudifier apps’ is a huge win for women’s rights and child protection,” said Dutch Green MEP Kim van Sparrentak after the vote.</p><p>“Every day, women across the EU are targeted by deep-nude AI tools that strip them of their dignity, intimidate them online and make them vulnerable to blackmail and abuse. We are finally stepping up against every person’s nightmare,” she added.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>MEPs also agreed on a <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2025/11/brussels-proposes-relaxing-data-protection-to-support-tech-firms/">Commission proposal</a> to simplify EU rules that classify AI systems based on risk, from minimal to prohibited, and to delay certain rules on high-risk systems ensuring that guidance is provided and companies are ready to apply them.</p><p>MEPs said from November 2 2026, instead of 2 February 2027 proposed by the commission, companies will have to watermark AI-created audio, image, video or text content to indicate its origin.</p><p>New rules will become effective on December 2 2027 for high-risk AI systems involving biometrics, critical infrastructure, education, employment, essential services, law enforcement, justice and border management.</p><p>The report passed with 569 votes in favour, 45 against and 23 abstentions. The parliament and the council, representing EU governments, now have to agree the final text.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/dutch-european-news/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/sexual-abuse/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/tech/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=265636</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 13:25:34 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Online home furnishings group Fonq declared bankrupt</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/03/online-home-furnishings-group-fonq-declared-bankrupt/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-265708 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-bankruptcy category-business"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Online home furnishings group Fonq declared bankrupt</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-03-27T13:15:34+00:00"> March 27, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-265709" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_265709"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1707" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/01-showroom-02-min-scaled.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/01-showroom-02-min-scaled.jpg 2560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/01-showroom-02-min-560x373.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/01-showroom-02-min-1200x800.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/01-showroom-02-min-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/01-showroom-02-min-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/01-showroom-02-min-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/01-showroom-02-min-2048x1365.jpg 2048w" width="2560"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-265709"> Photo: Fonq</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p data-end="184" data-start="0">Dutch online furniture and home products retailer <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Fonq</span></span> has been declared bankrupt. The group, which also owns the Naduvi platform, had applied for court protection from creditors just over a week ago.</p><p data-end="184" data-start="0">Customers have already been unable to place orders via the website for the past few days and those with outstanding orders may have lost their money, according to the Telegraaf.</p><p data-end="546" data-start="380">Fonq was founded in 2003 and operated webshops in the Netherlands, Belgium and Germany. In 2024, it expanded by acquiring rival <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Naduvi</span></span>.</p><p data-end="546" data-start="380"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="769" data-start="548">The company reported a loss of more than €14 million in 2023, and struggled to secure further financing, with shareholders stepping in after a bank declined further lending.</p><p data-end="984" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="" data-start="771">More than 250 employees are affected by the bankruptcy. The curators said they examining whether parts of the business can continue, but did not specify which divisions or whether there is interest from potential buyers.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/bankruptcy/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/business/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=265708</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 13:15:34 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Town may have to go back to the ballot box over possible fraud</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/03/town-may-have-to-go-back-to-the-ballot-box-over-possible-fraud/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-265662 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-fraud category-local-elections category-zuid-holland"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Town may have to go back to the ballot box over possible fraud</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-03-27T11:48:16+00:00"> March 27, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-259121" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_259121"> <img alt="Election, vote here, amsterdam" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1512" sizes="(max-width: 2016px) 100vw, 2016px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IMG_0573.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IMG_0573.jpg 2016w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IMG_0573-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IMG_0573-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IMG_0573-768x576.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/IMG_0573-1536x1152.jpg 1536w" width="2016"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-259121"> Photo: Dutch News</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The inhabitants of Gorinchem in Zuid-Holland may have to return to the ballot box due to possible election fraud, local media <a href="https://www.rijnmond.nl/nieuws/2172567/gemeenteraad-gorinchem-moet-zelf-beslissen-over-herstemming-kiesraad-is-niet-voor-of-tegen">reported.</a></p><p>Mayor Reinie Melissant was told of 10 signs pointing to potential fraud by staff at several voting locations.</p><p>At one location, 135 of the 650 votes were cast by proxy, which is a “relatively high number”. One of the candidates came to the same polling station five times, each time accompanied by one or two voters armed with proxy votes.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>An initial investigation by police confirmed possible fraud. Melissant told local media that people had been “approached by phone and pressurised into allowing others to vote for them”, which is a criminal offence.</p><p>The council must now decide if the elections have to be redone although the Kiesraad, the body which supervises the election process, said a repeat would present its own problems.</p><p>“A partial of complete repeat of the vote is very rare and far-reaching,” the Kiesraad told the council in a letter. “Voters can adapt their vote based on the results of the first ballot and not everyone who voted the first time around may be willing or able to cast their vote again,” the letter said.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Local authorities expert John Bijl said the the council faced a dilemma. “The results could change. But if the council doesn’t call another election the suspicion will remain,” he said.</p><p>The council will vote about holding a new election on Monday, which will then have to take place within the next 30 days.</p><p>Local party Democraten Gorinchem won seven seats on the town council in last week’s election, with another local party Stadsbelang winning four. D66, the VVD and GroenLinks-PvdA each won three on the 25-seat council.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/fraud/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/local-elections/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/zuid-holland/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=265662</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 11:48:16 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Suriname fails to make World Cup dreams come true</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/03/suriname-fails-to-make-world-cup-dreams-come-true/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-265689 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-football category-sport category-world-cup-2026"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Suriname fails to make World Cup dreams come true</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-03-27T11:39:14+00:00"> March 27, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-265690" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_265690"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/ANP-554445011.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/ANP-554445011.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/ANP-554445011-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/ANP-554445011-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/ANP-554445011-768x512.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-265690"> Suriname's Myenty Abena, left, and Gyrano Kerk at the end of the game. Photo: Fernando Llano via ANP</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p data-end="246" data-start="86">The former Dutch colony of Suriname has failed to win one of the last tickets to this summer’s World Cup after losing the play-off semi-finals 2-1 to Bolivia.</p><p data-end="394" data-start="248">Suriname took the lead just after the break with a goal from Liam van Gelderen, but Bolivia managed to score twice towards the end of the match.</p><p data-end="618" data-start="396">“We played well but we missed the chances we had and we gave away cheap goals,” said coach Henk ten Cate after the game. “They were in possession of the ball a lot more than we were, but we had the better opportunities.”</p><p data-end="618" data-start="396"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="793" data-start="620">The former Dutch colony of Curaçao, now an independent country within the Kingdom of the Netherlands, qualified for the tournament for the first time last year.</p><p data-end="1014" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="" data-start="795">Curaçao, with a population of 155,000, is the smallest nation ever to reach the tournament. They will meet Germany in their first group match, while the Netherlands will take on Japan.</p><p data-end="1014" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="" data-start="795">The World Cup will take place in Mexico, Canada and the US between June 11 and July 19.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/football/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/sport/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/football/world-cup-2026/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=265689</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 11:39:14 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>36,000 same-sex couples have tied the knot in 25 years in NL</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/03/36000-same-sex-couples-have-tied-the-knot-in-25-years-in-nl/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-265666 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-lgbtqi category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> 36,000 same-sex couples have tied the knot in 25 years in NL</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-03-27T09:48:38+00:00"> March 27, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-174798" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_174798"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Depositphotos_10545739_s-2019.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Depositphotos_10545739_s-2019.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Depositphotos_10545739_s-2019-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Depositphotos_10545739_s-2019-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Depositphotos_10545739_s-2019-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Depositphotos_10545739_s-2019-640x427.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Depositphotos_10545739_s-2019-92x62.jpg 92w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Depositphotos_10545739_s-2019-130x87.jpg 130w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-174798"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p data-end="236" data-start="0">On April 1 it will be 25 years since the Netherlands became the first country in the world to legalise same-sex marriage and since then 36,000 couples have tied the knot, according to new figures from the national statistics agency CBS.</p><p data-end="470" data-start="238">By the start of this year, the Netherlands had 25,000 married same-sex couples – almost 12,000 men and 13,000 women. Of them, 600 male couples and 500 female couples were among those to get married in the first year of legalisation.</p><p data-end="581" data-start="472">Men were on average aged 41 when they got married while women and mixed-sex couples had an average age of 37.</p><p data-end="581" data-start="472"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="807" data-start="583">Every year some 400 same-sex marriages end and women are almost twice as likely to get divorced as men. Of the women who married in 2015, 24% were divorced 10 years later, compared with 13% of male couples and mixed couples.</p><p data-end="881" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="" data-start="809">Most same-sex married couples live in Amsterdam, Nijmegen and Groningen.</p><ul><li data-end="881" data-start="809"><a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2023/08/inburgering-with-dn-key-moments-in-dutch-lgbtq-history/">Inburgering with DN: Key moments in LGBTQ+ history</a></li></ul><p data-end="881" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="" data-start="809">An increasing number of same-sex couples are also parents, the CBS said. Some 9,000 female and almost 1,000 male couples have at least one child living at home.</p><p data-end="881" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="" data-start="809">The Netherlands was the world’s first country to legalise marriages between people of the same sex, followed by Belgium, Spain, Canada and South Africa.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/lgbtqi/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=265666</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 09:48:38 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Brussels agrees new handling fee for parcels from outside the EU</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/03/brussels-agrees-new-handling-fee-for-parcels-from-outside-the-eu/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-265661 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-business category-dutch-european-news category-retail"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Brussels agrees new handling fee for parcels from outside the EU</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-03-27T09:28:12+00:00"> March 27, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-195561" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_195561"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Depositphotos_389002474_S.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Depositphotos_389002474_S.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Depositphotos_389002474_S-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Depositphotos_389002474_S-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Depositphotos_389002474_S-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Depositphotos_389002474_S-640x427.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Depositphotos_389002474_S-92x62.jpg 92w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Depositphotos_389002474_S-130x87.jpg 130w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-195561"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p data-end="261" data-start="0">The European Union has agreed to introduce a new handling fee for small parcels from outside the bloc, aimed primarily at curbing the surge in low-cost imports from Chinese webshops such as <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Temu</span></span> and <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Shein</span></span>.</p><p data-end="518" data-start="263">EU member states and the European parliament reached the agreement on Thursday as part of a wider overhaul of customs rules. The measures are intended to protect European businesses and help customs authorities cope with the sharp rise in small shipments.</p><p data-end="972" data-start="709">The level of the new charge will be set later by the European Commission, but officials expect it to amount to a few euros per parcel. The charge is likely to take effect from November 1 and comes on top of an earlier <a href="https://ec.europa.eu/commission/presscorner/detail/en/ip_25_3045">€3 customs fee</a> per package worth less than €150 which is due to be introduced in July.</p><p data-end="972" data-start="709"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="707" data-start="520">In 2025, more than 5.5 billion parcels worth under €150 entered the EU, more than double the number in 2023. Every day, around one million such packages arrive in the Netherlands, of which 80% to 90% come from Chinese mail order firms.</p><p data-end="1229" data-start="974">Online retailers will be responsible for paying the levy to customs authorities, and it will be policed by spot checks and fines. Part of the income will go to national governments, with the remainder allocated to the EU budget.</p><p data-end="257" data-start="100">In January the Dutch government said it will not bring in an extra charge on parcels from outside the EU, because Belgium and France had abandoned their plans, and Brussels brought forward its own tariffs.</p><p data-end="928" data-is-last-node="" data-is-only-node="" data-start="826">EU research suggests that up to 65% of small parcels entering the EU are undervalued and avoid duties.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/business/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/dutch-european-news/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/retail/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=265661</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 09:28:12 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Dutch discounter Action plans to open stores in the US</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/03/dutch-discounter-action-plans-to-open-stores-in-the-us/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-265658 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-business category-retail"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Dutch discounter Action plans to open stores in the US</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-03-27T09:00:45+00:00"> March 27, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-112697" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_112697"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Action-discount-store.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Action-discount-store.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Action-discount-store-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Action-discount-store-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Action-discount-store-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/Action-discount-store-300x200.jpg 300w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-112697"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p data-end="212" data-start="0">Dutch discount chain <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">Action</span></span> is planning to <a href="https://company.action.com/pressreleases/action-results-2025-strong-growth-and-progress-sustainability-programme/">expand into the United States</a>, with the first store expected to open by the end of next year or early 2028, the company said at the presentation of its 2025 results.</p><p data-end="461" data-start="214">The retailer, based in Zwaagdijk in Noord-Holland, aims to grow to around 100 stores in the US by the end of 2030. The first outlet is likely to open in the south-eastern United States, with preparations under way to establish a local organisation later this year.</p><p data-end="672" data-start="463">Action said it will follow the same “disciplined and step-by-step approach” in the US as it has used in its European expansion.</p><p data-end="672" data-start="463"><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div></p><p data-end="889" data-start="674">The chain opened its first store in Enkhuizen in 1993 and now operates more than 3,300 outlets across 14 countries in Europe. Earlier this month, it launched its first shops in Croatia, with Slovenia set to follow after the summer and Bulgaria next year.</p><p data-end="1096" data-start="891">To support its growth, the company plans to open three new distribution centres this year in Italy, Spain and France.</p><p data-end="1096" data-start="891">The company booked net sales of €16 billion in 2025, up 16% on 2024. Like for like sales rose 4.9%. Action has been owned by British investment firm <span class="hover:entity-accent entity-underline inline cursor-pointer align-baseline"><span class="whitespace-normal">3i Group since 2011.</span></span></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/business/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/retail/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=265658</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 09:00:45 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Fishmonger faces court after refusing to sell to woman in niqab</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/03/fishmonger-faces-court-after-refusing-to-sell-to-woman-in-niqab/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-265640 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-court-cases category-discrimination"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Fishmonger faces court after refusing to sell to woman in niqab</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-03-27T08:42:20+00:00"> March 27, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-100020" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_100020"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="297" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/woman-niqab.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/woman-niqab.jpg 500w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/woman-niqab-300x178.jpg 300w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/woman-niqab-244x144.jpg 244w" width="500"/></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The public prosecution must pursue a case against a fishmonger who refused to serve a woman wearing a niqab, a court in The Hague has <a href="https://uitspraken.rechtspraak.nl/details?id=ECLI:NL:GHDHA:2026:370&amp;showbutton=true&amp;keyword=niqab%2Bden%2Bhaag&amp;idx=1">ruled.</a></p><p>The incident happened four years ago at a fishmonger’s in Hoek van Holland where she wanted to order some <em>kibbeling</em>, or fried fish. The fishmonger said he did not want to serve the woman because he could not see her face, which he claimed was “against his rules”. He also ordered her to leave his shop.</p><p>The woman, who filmed the encounter on her mobile phone, subsequently reported the man to the police for discrimination but the public prosecution office decided there was no enough evidence of a criminal offence to warrant prosecution.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The woman then successfully appealed, stating that she had been treated differently because of her faith and dress. The court dismissed the OM’s argument that the woman was refused service because her face was hidden and not because she was a Muslim.</p><p>The court also said a ruling on the case could create clarity in the shape of a legal precedent for similar situations.</p><p>In the Netherlands, clothing which cover the face, such as a niqab, is <a href="https://www.rijksoverheid.nl/onderwerpen/gezichtsbedekkende-kleding-in-de-media-boerkaverbod/gezichtsbedekkende-kleding-gedeeltelijk-verbieden">banned</a> in schools, public transport, care facilities and government buildings.</p><p>The fishmonger was not present at the ruling to tell his side of the story. The man referred to the video and only wants to present his arguments in front of the judge, he said.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/court-cases/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/discrimination/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=265640</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 08:42:20 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Less sleep ahead: the clocks go forward on Saturday night</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2026/03/less-sleep-ahead-the-clocks-go-forward-on-saturday-night/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-265653 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-uncategorized"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Less sleep ahead: the clocks go forward on Saturday night</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2026-03-27T08:38:38+00:00"> March 27, 2026 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-66547" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_66547"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="283" sizes="(max-width: 424px) 100vw, 424px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/summertime-clocks-forward.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/summertime-clocks-forward.jpg 424w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/summertime-clocks-forward-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/summertime-clocks-forward-300x200.jpg 300w" width="424"/></figure><main class="px-4"><p class="" data-end="162" data-start="69">The clocks go forward one hour on Saturday night as the Netherlands moves into summer time.</p><p class="" data-end="296" data-start="164">The shift always takes place on the last weekend in March, while the clocks go back to winter time on the last weekend in October.</p><p class="" data-end="458" data-start="298">According to weather bureau KNMI, the weekend will be chillier than of late, with temperatures no higher than 12° and a mix of sunshine, cloud, and rain.</p><p data-end="809" data-start="603">It will become drier and slightly warmer towards the end of next week</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/uncategorized/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=265653</guid><pubDate>Fri, 27 Mar 2026 08:38:38 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item></channel></rss>